    "recap_headline": "University of Houston Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HOUSTON \u2013\nHouston Baseball dropped its first extra-inning contest of the season, 6-3, to #25 Louisiana at Don Sanders Field at Darryl and Lori Schroeder Park on Wednesday night.\nSophomore\nKendall Hoffman\n(1-2) took the loss for Houston (12-8), ceding three runs in his first relief appearance of the year. Cody Brasch (2-1) picked up the victory for Louisiana (16-5) by tossing the last 2.2 shutout innings for the Cajuns.\nPLAYER HIGHLIGHTS\nTre Broussard\n: 2-4, 2B, RBI, BB\nRiley Jackson\n: 1-2, HR, RBI, R, 2 BB\nAlex Solis\n: 3.0 IP, 1 H, 0 R, 1 BB, 0 K\nNOTABLES\nFreshman\nCaden Cooper\nearned his first career appearance with five-or-more strikeouts.\nHouston turned its 16\nth\ndouble play of the season.\nThe Cougars played in their first extra-inning game since April 9, 2025.\nGAME SUMMARY\nHouston grabbed the first lead of the game with a solo homer from junior\nRiley Jackson\nin the bottom of the second. Louisiana answered with a two-spot in its half of the third to take the lead.\nAfter the Cajuns added another run in the fourth to take a 3-1 edge, the Cougars cut their deficit to one with an RBI single off the bat of junior\nTre Broussard\nthat drove home sophomore\nMcClane Helton\n. Houston went on to even the score in the eighth as redshirt sophomore\nXavier Perez\nscored on a single from senior\nCarsten Sabathia III\n.\nHeading into the opening frame of extras, Louisiana jumped on its first opportunity. The Cajuns plated three runs in the top of the 10\nth\n, with two being unearned due to a Houston error. The Cougars couldn't find the equalizer in the bottom of the frame, giving Louisiana the 6-3 victory.\nUP NEXT\nHouston plays its first Big 12 Conference road series as it heads to Kansas for a three-game set. The teams meet to start the weekend at 6 p.m. Friday and continue at 2 p.m. Saturday before a 1 p.m. Sunday conclusion.\nSUPPORT THE COUGARS\nFans can make a direct impact on the success of Houston Baseball by\nproviding NIL opportunities\nand by\njoining the Dugout Club\nwhich provides financial support directly to Houston Baseball for needs beyond its operating budget.\nSTAY CONNECTED\nFans can receive updates by following\n@UHCougarBB\non X, formerly known as Twitter, and catch up with the latest news and notes on the team by clicking LIKE on the team's Facebook page at\nHouston Cougar Baseball\n. Fans can also follow the team on Instagram at\n@uhcougarbb\n.\n\u2013 UHCougars.com \u2013"
